name: source_desc
description: Source of data (CENSUS or SURVEY). Census program includes the Census of Ag as well as follow up projects. Survey program includes national, state, and county surveys.

name: sector_desc
description: Five high level, broad categories useful to narrow down choices (CROPS, ANIMALS & PRODUCTS, ECONOMICS, DEMOGRAPHICS, and ENVIRONMENTAL).

name: group_desc
description: Subsets within sector (e.g., under sector = CROPS, the groups are FIELD CROPS, FRUIT & TREE NUTS, HORTICULTURE, and VEGETABLES).

name: commodity_desc
description: The primary subject of interest (e.g., CORN, CATTLE, LABOR, TRACTORS, OPERATORS).

name: class_desc
description: Generally a physical attribute (e.g., variety, size, color, gender) of the commodity.

name: prodn_practice_desc
description: A method of production or action taken on the commodity (e.g., IRRIGATED, ORGANIC, ON FEED).

name: util_practice_desc
description: Utilizations (e.g., GRAIN, FROZEN, SLAUGHTER) or marketing channels (e.g., FRESH MARKET, PROCESSING, RETAIL).

name: statisticcat_desc
description: The aspect of a commodity being measured (e.g., AREA HARVESTED, PRICE RECEIVED, INVENTORY, SALES).

name: unit_desc
description: The unit associated with the statistic category (e.g., ACRES, $ / LB, HEAD, $, OPERATIONS).

name: short_desc
description: A concatenation of six columns: commodity_desc, class_desc, prodn_practice_desc, util_practice_desc, statisticcat_desc, and unit_desc.

name: domain_desc
description: Generally another characteristic of operations that produce a particular commodity (e.g., ECONOMIC CLASS, AREA OPERATED, NAICS CLASSIFICATION, SALES). For chemical usage data, the domain describes the type of chemical applied to the commodity. The domain = TOTAL will have no further breakouts; i.e., the data value pertains completely to the short_desc.

name: domaincat_desc
description: Categories or partitions within a domain (e.g., under domain = SALES, domain categories include $1,000 TO $9,999, $10,000 TO $19,999, etc).

name: agg_level_desc
description: Aggregation level or geographic granularity of the data (e.g., STATE, AG DISTRICT, COUNTY, REGION, ZIP CODE).

name: state_ansi
description: American National Standards Institute (ANSI) standard 2-digit state codes.

name: state_fips_code
description: NASS 2-digit state codes; include 99 and 98 for US TOTAL and OTHER STATES, respectively; otherwise match ANSI codes.

name: state_alpha
description: State abbreviation, 2-character alpha code.

name: state_name
description: State full name.

name: asd_code
description: NASS defined county groups, unique within a state, 2-digit ag statistics district code.

name: asd_desc
description: Ag statistics district name.

name: county_ansi
description: ANSI standard 3-digit county codes.

name: county_code
description: NASS 3-digit county codes; includes 998 for OTHER (COMBINED) COUNTIES and Alaska county codes; otherwise match ANSI codes.

name: county_name
description: County name.

name: region_desc
description: NASS defined geographic entities not readily defined by other standard geographic levels. A region can be a less than a state (SUB-STATE) or a group of states (MULTI-STATE), and may be specific to a commodity.

name: zip_5
description: US Postal Service 5-digit zip code.

name: watershed_code
description: US Geological Survey (USGS) 8-digit Hydrologic Unit Code (HUC) for watersheds.

name: watershed_desc
description: Name assigned to the HUC.

name: congr_district_code
description: US Congressional District 2-digit code.

name: country_code
description: US Census Bureau, Foreign Trade Division 4-digit country code, as of April, 2007.

name: country_name
description: Country name.

name: location_desc
description: Full description for the location dimension.

name: year
description: The numeric year of the data.

name: freq_desc
description: Length of time covered (ANNUAL, SEASON, MONTHLY, WEEKLY, POINT IN TIME). MONTHLY often covers more than one month. POINT IN TIME is as of a particular day.

name: begin_code
description: If applicable, a 2-digit code corresponding to the beginning of the reference period (e.g., for freq_desc = MONTHLY, begin_code ranges from 01 (January) to 12 (December)).

name: end_code
description: If applicable, a 2-digit code corresponding to the end of the reference period (e.g., the reference period of JAN THRU MAR will have begin_code = 01 and end_code = 03).

name: reference_period_desc
description: The specific time frame, within a freq_desc.

name: week_ending
description: Week ending date, used when freq_desc = WEEKLY.

name: load_time
description: Date and time indicating when record was inserted into Quick Stats database.

name: value
description: Published data value.

name: cv_percent
description: Coefficient of variation. Available for the 2012 Census of Agriculture only. County-level CVs are generalized.
